ZCZC GE30
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 082300 UTC
LATE ON SUNDAY AND OVERNIGHT A MAJOR RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE IS EXP TO DOMINATE THE WERN ATLANTIC AND UK
WHILE A SHALLOW LOW WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE AROUND 1010 IS
EXP OVER SERN NORWAY. INTO THE NEW WORKING WEEK THE LOW
IS LIKELY TO DEEPEN IN SITU NEARING 1000 MIDDAY MONDAY
BEFORE THE WHOLE PRESSURE PATTERN BEGINS TO PROGRESS. BY
THE END OF THE PERIOD THE MAIN AXIS OF THE HIGH SHOULD
LIE FM THE AZORES TO THE UK WITH SCANDINAVIA PERHAPS
RETAINING A SHALLOW LOW OF AROUND 1010. NO HAZARDOUS
WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS CULLERCOATS. HOWEVER THERE IS A
VERY LOW RISK OF OCCASIONAL NEAR GALES DEVELOPING ACROSS
S UTSIRE AND FISHER THROUGH MONDAY EASING ON TUESDAY AS
SIMILAR WINDS POSSIBLY DEVELOP ACROSS THE ENGLISH CHANNEL
SEA AREAS LATER. BY WEDNESDAY ALL OF CULLERCOATS IS
LIKELY TO HAVE REVERTED TO NO HAZARDOUS WINDS
